            <div class="mainBodyText">
                <span class="fs5"><!-- OldURL: http://boards2.parentsplace.com/messages/get/pplibchristiann15/22.html -->
<p>Lurker - could use some help/guidance &lt;m&gt;</p>

Hi all.
<P>

I don't really lurk here regularly, but wanted to pop in to see if you guys could help me. I AM a regular poster on the atheist board and lurk on RD, so lots of your names are familiar to me.
<P>

The short version: I was raised fundamentalist Assembly of God and then grew up, got educated (in the sciences, no less) and tossed all that baggage. I have not found my way clear to re-establishing a belief in God, but certainly believe that my life would be easier if I could find a way to rationalize it in my head, in some form or another. We live in the Bible Belt and have young children; I would love the community of a church; there is a certain peace and joy to be found within a circle of belief and believers; etc. I can almost JUUUUST wrap my head around pantheism, which gives me hope that maybe there is something interesting out there. And, truthfully, I really am a very spiritual person, either b/c of the way I was raised or b/c of temperament, and I do sometimes (mostly around the holidays, of course) feel that my life would be richer if I had some kind of belief system that I could share with others, something that wouldn't compromise my value system. It's this last bit that's been the sticking point, as my value system is heavy on reason and empathy &amp; compassion, some things that Chrisitianity as I experienced it have not been real big on. (I just reread that last sentence. Sad, isn't it? But even reading on RD reinforces that - there are just some very mean-spirited believers there, aren't there?!? Some very bitter fruit there, indeed.)
<P>

What I am looking for is some reading that will help me recast Christianity into at least a neutral light, and maybe even a positive one for me. Every time I go to pick up the Bible, it's just this very negative, literalist experience - I need another lens to see this all through. Can anyone provide some ideas for me? Not sure where this will lead; at the very least, maybe it'll help me work through some of the lingering antagonism I still feel towards fundamentalist Christianity. That can only be a good thing.
<P>

TIA,
<P>

Carrie

<P>

</span>
