            <div class="mainBodyText">
                <span class="fs5"><!-- OldURL: http://boards2.parentsplace.com/messages/get/pplibchristiann15/22/2.html -->
<p>Hi Carrie, and welcome.....m</p>

Glad you stopped by.
<P>

A couple of suggestions for you might be John Shelby Sponge or Marcus Borg.  
<P>

Specifically I'm thinking of...
<P>

Rescuing the Bible from Fundamentalism: A Bishop Rethinks the Meaning of Scripture by John Shelby Spong 
<P>

<A HREF="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0060675187/qid=1041381966/sr=8-2/ref=sr_8_2/103-1153130-8776614?v=glance&s=books&n=507846">http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0060675187/qid=1041381966/sr=8-2/ref=sr_8_2/103-1153130-8776614?v=glance&amp;s=books&amp;n=507846</A>
<P>

or
<P>

Why Christianity Must Change or Die: A Bishop Speaks to Believers In Exile
by John Shelby Spong 
<P>

<A HREF="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0060675365/ref=pd_bxgy_text_1/103-1153130-8776614?v=glance&s=books">http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0060675365/ref=pd_bxgy_text_1/103-1153130-8776614?v=glance&amp;s=books</A>
<P>

or a bit of a different spin but still good.  
<P>

Reading the Bible Again for the First Time: Taking the Bible Seriously But Not Literally
by Marcus J. Borg
<P>

<A HREF="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0060609184/qid=1041382155/sr=1-3/ref=sr_1_3/103-1153130-8776614?v=glance&s=books">http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0060609184/qid=1041382155/sr=1-3/ref=sr_1_3/103-1153130-8776614?v=glance&amp;s=books</A>
<P>

Those might be worth looking at for you.  I haven't read Sponge but I've wanted to and will some day.  You will find that both these authors (also both clergy and Borg is a professor) are far from fundamentalist, but are faithful Christians who can think and leave room for doubt and questioning without compromising their faith.  
<P>

Hope you'll stick around and 'chat' with us.  Feel free to participate in our bible studies if you would like to, even if it's just to express discontent with the text!  I for one love to hear what non-believers think and the discussion that comes from it.  (and I know I'm not alone in that)
<P>

Happy New Year too!
<P>

Elaine

<P>

