            <div class="mainBodyText">
                <span class="fs5"><!-- OldURL: http://boards2.parentsplace.com/messages/get/pplibchristiann15/22/2/2/1.html -->
<p>Where did you hear about this book? It's such a coincidence...</p>

I was reading a book I bought last week, "Saving Jesus from the Christians" by Clayton Sullivan (who is a Southern Baptist preacher, of all things, and on faculty at Southern Miss) and he mentioned that work several times, very favorably. I'm looking for it, too. Also, I highly recommend the book I just read (noted above) for anyone interested in taking an honest look at their faith and at the bible. I don't necessarily agree with everything the author says, but it really showed me a lot of areas where I *should* have asked questions, but didn't. I with Ouro would read it, because I'd like to have a review from his POV. Heck, I'd like to hear *everyone's* opinion on it! He really takes the rose colored glasses off when looking at Christianity and at Jesus, but still manages to show why it is worthwhile.

<P>

</span>
